title: Halo Cole Protocol 7
content:
Kincaide used the third man, a rioter, as a shield. He shoved the surprised civilian into Watanabe, then shot them both several times with a plasma rifle. Keyes felt sick as he watched Watanabe
fall. The man may have been ONI, but he was crew and a fellow soldier, and Keyes realized he was screaming.

Watanabe groaned, and Keyes crawled over to him. The plasma rifle had ripped through the ONI agent's left torso, leaving a crisped mess. Keyes gagged at the smell. "This is bad," Watanabe muttered.

"Don't move," Keyes told him. “Stay still, don't close your eyes."

"It hurts."

Keyes bit his lip. “Just hang in there, Akio. They're on their way. We just need to hang in there." Hansen fired three shots at someone in the stairway trying their luck. Watanabe grabbed Keyes's forearm and grimaced, then let go. Keyes looked down at the limp, dead body of Major Akio Watanabe.-Chpt.16

title: Halo Cole Protocol 6
content: "Listen up!" Keyes held up his newly acquired plasma rifle as he shouted. "Anyone else tries storming the roof, I'll blow their damn heads off too." He fired the plasma rifle twice into the base of the ladder, and watched with satisfaction as metal slumped and the ladder slid off the side of the building, falling over toward the crowd. Rioters scattered as it struck the street in their midst.-Chpt.16

title: Halo Cole Protocol 5
content:
Keyes shot him in the chest, then stomach, grazed his side, and then ran out of ammunition. He slammed into Kincaide, grappling for the alien rifle. "Damn. . . UNSC ... pig,” Kincaide spat, still trying to force the rifle up into Keyes's ribs. “Go back to Earth. You don't belong here." The memory of the explosions in the cargo bay of Finnegan's Wake, the flaming Pelican Jeffries piloted going down, wounded ODSTs gritting their teeth and bearing the pain as they waited for
help, all filled Keyes's mind. He grunted and kept forcing the plas- ma rifle down until it was aimed at Kincaide's feet.

He pulled the trigger, and a burst of white-hot plasma destroyed the Insurrectionist's leg and threw Keyes back, still holding onto the rifle.
Concrete bubbled where they'd stood, and Keyes felt the legs of his uniform burning. He patted the fires out quickly, and looked back at Kincaide.
The man had lost his left leg, blown clean off at the thigh. He'd been shot in the shoulder and chest.

Yet he now had a small pistol in his right hand, lifting it up to point it at Keyes with determination in his glazed eyes. Without hesitation, Keyes blew the Insurrectionist's head off his body with a burst of plasma. His hands shook. He'd never shot a man before. He'd shot at
people, fired warning shots, practiced in drills, but never actually looked at someone in the eyes who was about to kill him, and beat him to the draw.-Chpt.16

title: Halo Cole Protocol 3
content: Thel looked his guards over. Lean and tall, their muted brown skin was almost all hidden by sturdy armor. Covenant armor. Their long-necked heads were sheathed in chain mail, and their large eyes gleamed in the flickering light of the hall. They were all well built, powerful, overly trained since birth, specimens of Sangheili warriors.-Chpt.9

title: Halo Cole Protocol 2
content:
"What happened to you? Looks like something ran you over."

"Think I'm in bad shape?" Melko coughed. "Should see the other guy." Delgado kept his back to the container, gun aimed at the edge. "You killed one of them?"

"We turned the corner at the same time." Melko stepped back, chancing a glance around the other side of the container. He held his handgun in his right hand while his left clenched his stomach.
"I fired first. I fired second. I fired the third time, too."

"Where'd the blood come from?"

"One of the other Jackals fired fourth."

Delgado shook his head. This had gotten out of control. He reached in his pocket and pulled out the instigator of all their troubles: a tiny chip, lying in the heart of a toughened case just smaller
than his thumb.-Prologue

title: Halo Cole Protocol 1
content:
Ignatio Delgado ducked behind a bulkhead next to a set of cargo containers, the red paint peeling off their ribbed metal surfaces, just as a burst of plasma hit. The dull metal he hid behind glowed-hot tiny molten gobs dripping then spitting as they hit the cold deck near his feet.

The spiny quilled mohawks on their skulls twitched. The sound of plasma shots hit the other side of the container and reverberated through the hold.-Prologue

title: world building - guilder
content:
** Political Structure
-> How are decisions made, by whom how is the territory organized
-> Corruption
-> Diplomatic Policy
-> Social Movements (Units, radicalist, opposition party)
-> Information (Where does its information come from, how do people in the nation get information (newspapers, letters, etc)
-> School system (education, who is taught, who are they taught by, what do they learn)
-> Languages (what do they speak, different legal or court languages, who can read/write)
-> Military (How powerful is it, what is it composed of, who leads it)
-> Energy (Do they have power, electricity, steam, etc how it it produced)

** Economy
-> What type of economy is it
-> How is wealth created
-> What types of services / industry does it have
-> What trade doe sit have, who does it trade with, how it it organized
-> What is its currency
-> Does it have establish finances

** Culture
-> What music do the people listen to, what instruments do they use
-> Food (National specialities, what do they eat day-to-day, what is cheap, what is expensive, what is reserved for elites)
-> Houses (How do they live, communally/individually, what is their architecture
-> Clothes (What do people wear, what trends do they follow, what is their clothing made from, describe their fashion)
-> Sports (Do they have sports, what do they play and why
-> Relationships (How are their relationships structured, their views on marriage, sex, etc)
-> What are their Taboos
-> What is their ethnicity, are they multicultural
-> What is their religion, how important is it, day-to-day practices, what is its influence/political sway.


** Life
-> What is their quality of life relative to other nations (Employment, income, medical access, infrastructure, cost of living, speech)
-> What are their economical or social classes

==========================================================================

-- Describe the geography where your nation calls home.

-- Describe the climate, how severe are their seasons

-- Do they have natural disasters, how often, how do they deal with them.

-- What importance (spiritual or cultural) is their geography

-- How do people feel about landscapes being altered beyond what is traditional.

-- What are the most commonly grown foods.

-- What are the most commonly eaten foods.

-- What foods are considered exotic or expensive.

-- What forms of alcohol are common, or rare.

-- Is there enough food and water for the population without imports.

-- What is the places most abundant natural resource.

-- What is its most valuable resource.

-- What resource is the most lacking.

-- How do people travel from one place to another within the city.

-- How do people travel from the city to other places.

-- Are the borders secure? How are they secured?

-- How many people live in the society?

-- Where in this place do they congregate?

-- What are the most common domesticated animals here? What are they domesticated for?

-- What are the most common wild animals? How are wild animals treated?

-- What animals are likely to be pets? Which ones wont be?

-- What are the most domesticated plants? What are they used for?

-- What are the wild plants? What are they used for?

==================================================================

How far back does this societies written history go?

How far back does it believe it goes?

How was the society founded? Who founded in and under what circumstances?

What are the chief powers at the the time the society was founded?

What is the worst disaster they've ever faced?

What are some major events in this cultures past?

What was the best things that ever happened to them?

What in their past makes them feel ashamed?

What in their past makes them feel proud?

How strongly are people attached to their heritage?

What do they assume the future will hold?

How has this society changed?

What are the most popular stories told? Who is their greatest hero and greatest villain?

Do people believe the future will be better or worst than the present

================================================================

What are the races found in the city?

What are the different ethnic groups, how are they distributed?

How do they differ by language, appearance, or ancestry?

Are jobs divided by ethnicity? Are groups prejudiced by racial or ethnic heritage?

=================================================================

How many spouses can a man or woman have?

Who decides on marriage?

Can marriage end in divorce? How?

Who usually takes custody of children in a marriage?

How are families named?

What happens to orphans?

How are boy and girls treated differently, if at all?

What is considered a good marriage gift?

Does the society connect ideas of marriage with love?

How big are families, typically?

What constitutes a household? How many people live in a household, how many generations?

==================================================

What are their sins?

What professions or activities are considered feminine?

What makes someone a bad ruler? What can be done about it?

title: webtv mame launcher
content:
import sys, os, re, subprocess, ctypes, shutil, random
import winreg, win32gui, win32process, win32con, win32pipe, win32file, pywintypes
from PyQt5.QtWidgets import *
from PyQt5.QtCore import *
from PyQt5.QtGui import *
import socket, time
import threading


# Mapping of machine codes to human-readable names
MACHINE_NAMES = {
    "wtv1bf0": "WebTV Classic (2MB)",
    "wtv1bfe": "WebTV Classic (Prototype)",
    "wtv1dev": "WebTV Classic Dev Box (4MB)",
    "wtv1dv2": "WebTV Classic Dev Box (2MB)",
    "wtv1pal": "WebTV Classic (PAL)",

    "wtv2drb": "WebTV Plus (Derby)",
    "wtv2lc2": "WebTV Plus (LC2)",
    "wtv2dev": "WebTV Plus (Virtual 16MB Dev)",
    "wtv2esr": "WebTV Echostar",
    "wtv2jpc": "WebTV Classic (Japan)",
    "wtv2jpp": "WebTV Plus (Japan)",
    "wtv2ncl": "WebTV New Classic (BPS, 8MB)",
    "wtv2npl": "WebTV New Plus (16MB)",
    "wtv2utv": "Ultimate TV",
    "wtv2uvd": "Ultimate TV Dev Box (Fake)",
    "wtv2wld": "WebTV Italian Prototype"
}

class MameWorker(QThread):
    window_found = pyqtSignal(int)  # Signal to send back the HWND

    def __init__(self, command, parent=None):
        super().__init__(parent)
        self.command = command
        self.mame_hwnd = None
        self.process = None
        self._should_stop = False

    def run(self):
        # Launch MAME process
        self.process = subprocess.Popen(self.command)
        pid = self.process.pid

        # Try to find the MAME window
        for _ in range(30):  # Try for ~3 seconds
            hwnd = self._find_window_by_pid(pid)
            if hwnd:
                self.mame_hwnd = hwnd
                self.window_found.emit(hwnd)
                break
            time.sleep(0.1)

        self.process.wait()

    def stop(self):
        self._should_stop = True
        if self.process and self.process.poll() is None:
            self.process.terminate()
            try:
                self.process.wait(timeout=5)
            except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:
                self.process.kill()

    def _find_window_by_pid(self, target_pid):
        def callback(hwnd, pid_list):
            if win32gui.IsWindowVisible(hwnd) and win32gui.IsWindowEnabled(hwnd):
                _, pid = win32process.GetWindowThreadProcessId(hwnd)
                if pid == target_pid:
                    pid_list.append(hwnd)
        hwnds = []
        win32gui.EnumWindows(callback, hwnds)
        return hwnds[0] if hwnds else None

    def send_key(self, key):
        try:
            pipe = win32pipe.CreateNamedPipe(
                r'\\.\pipe\mame_input',
                win32pipe.PIPE_ACCESS_OUTBOUND,
                win32pipe.PIPE_TYPE_MESSAGE | win32pipe.PIPE_WAIT,
                1, 65536, 65536,
                0,
                None
            )
            win32pipe.ConnectNamedPipe(pipe, None)
            win32file.WriteFile(pipe, (key + "\n").encode())
            win32pipe.DisconnectNamedPipe(pipe)
        except pywintypes.error as e:
            print("Pipe closed or failed:", e)
            win32file.CloseHandle(pipe)

class MainWindow(QMainWindow):
    append_text_signal = pyqtSignal(str)

    def closeEvent(self, event):
        self.stop_socket_server()
        if self.worker:
            self.stop_mame()
        super().closeEvent(event)  # Ensure default cleanup continues

    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.diskpath = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), "disks")
        self.setWindowTitle("WebTV MAME Launcher")
        self.setGeometry(100, 100, 400, 100)
        self.server_socket = None
        self.conn = None
        self.server_thread = None

 
        self.apply_dark_mode()

        # Create the Menu Bar
        self.create_menu_bar()

        main_widget = QWidget()
        self.settings = QSettings("zefie", "WebTVLauncher")
        self.setCentralWidget(main_widget)
        layout = QVBoxLayout()
        possible_executables = [
            "webtv.exe",
            "webtv",
            "webtv2.exe",
            "webtv2",
            "webtv1.exe",
            "webtv1",
        ]
        self.executable = None
        for prog in possible_executables:
            path = shutil.which(prog)
            if path:
                self.executable = path
                break
        if not self.executable:
            print("Could not find mame executable (webtv, webtv1, webtv2)(.exe)")
            exit(1)
            
        # Dropdown
        self.dropdown = QComboBox()
        pattern = r'\((wtv[^)]+)\)'
        data = subprocess.run([self.executable, '-listbios'], capture_output=True, text=True)
        matches = re.findall(pattern, data.stdout)
        # For each match, check MACHINE_NAMES for a friendly description
        items = []
        for m in matches:
            desc = MACHINE_NAMES.get(m, "")
            if desc:
                items.append(f"{m} - {desc}")
            else:
                items.append(m)
        self.dropdown.addItems(items)
        top_layout = QHBoxLayout()
        top_layout.setSizeConstraint(QLayout.SetFixedSize)
        sel_opt = QLabel("Select Machine:")
        top_layout.addWidget(sel_opt)
        ssid_static = QLabel("SSID:")
        ssid_static.setAlignment(Qt.AlignRight)
        top_layout.addWidget(ssid_static)
        self.ssid_label = QLabel("No SSID")
        top_layout.addWidget(self.ssid_label)
        layout.addLayout(top_layout)
        layout.addWidget(self.dropdown)

        # Checkboxes
        checkboxes_layout = QHBoxLayout()
        self.verbose = QCheckBox("Verbose")
        self.mamedebug = QCheckBox("MAME Debugger")
        self.serialdbg = QCheckBox("Serial Debug")
        self.diskboot = QCheckBox("Disk Boot")
        self.diskboot.setChecked(True)

        self.modem = QCheckBox("Modem")
        self.verbose.setChecked(True)
        self.modem.setChecked(True)
        self.mamedebug.setChecked(False)
        self.serialdbg.setChecked(True)
        self.bitblab = QLabel("BITB:")
        self.bitb = QLineEdit("touchppp.lan.zef:1122");
        checkboxes_layout.addWidget(self.verbose)
        checkboxes_layout.addWidget(self.mamedebug)
        checkboxes_layout.addWidget(self.serialdbg)
        checkboxes_layout.addWidget(self.modem)
        checkboxes_layout.addWidget(self.diskboot)
        bitb_layout = QHBoxLayout()
        bitb_layout.addWidget(self.bitblab)
        bitb_layout.addWidget(self.bitb)
        disk_layout = QHBoxLayout()
        self.disklab = QLabel("Disk:")
        self.disklab.hide()
        self.disk = QComboBox()
        self.scan_disk_list()
        
        bitb_layout.addWidget(self.disklab)
        bitb_layout.addWidget(self.disk)
        
        layout.addLayout(checkboxes_layout)
        layout.addLayout(bitb_layout)
        layout.addLayout(disk_layout)
        # Button
        self.button = QPushButton("Launch MAME")
        self.dropdown.currentTextChanged.connect(self.on_dropdown_changed)
        self.button.clicked.connect(self.on_button_click)
        self.modem.clicked.connect(self.on_modem_click)
        layout.addWidget(self.button)
        self.setMinimumWidth(1280)
        self.setMinimumHeight(792)
        # Multiline Text Area
        self.text_area = QTextEdit()
        self.text_area.setReadOnly(True)
        self.text_area.setContextMenuPolicy(Qt.CustomContextMenu)
        self.text_area.customContextMenuRequested.connect(self.show_text_area_context_menu)
        hbox = QHBoxLayout()
        self.mame_window = QWidget();
        self.mame_window.setFixedSize(800, 600)
        self.mame_window.setFocusPolicy(Qt.ClickFocus)
        self.mame_window.mousePressEvent = lambda event: self.mame_window.setFocus()
        self.mame_window.setStyleSheet("background-color: black; border: 1px solid #555;")
        hbox.addWidget(self.mame_window)
        hbox.addWidget(self.text_area)
        layout.addLayout(hbox)
        input_layout = QHBoxLayout()
        self.single_line_input = QLineEdit()
        self.send_button = QPushButton("Send")
        self.send_button.clicked.connect(lambda: self.send_serial_data(self.single_line_input.text()))
        input_layout.addWidget(self.single_line_input)
        input_layout.addWidget(self.send_button)
        self.single_line_input.returnPressed.connect(self.send_button.click)
        layout.addLayout(input_layout)
        main_widget.setLayout(layout)
        self.text_area.setVisible(self.serialdbg.isChecked())
        self.text_area.setStyleSheet("font-family: monospace; font-size: 8pt;")
        #self.text_area.setLineWrapMode(QTextEdit.NoWrap)
        self.text_area.setPlaceholderText("Serial output will appear here...")
        self.serialdbg.toggled.connect(self.toggleSerialDebug)
        self.append_text_signal.connect(self.handle_serial_data)
        self.text_area.autoFormattingEnabled = False
        self.load_settings()
        self.on_dropdown_changed()

    def show_text_area_context_menu(self, position):
        """Show context menu for the text area"""
        context_menu = QMenu(self)
        
        clear_action = QAction("Clear Output", self)
        clear_action.triggered.connect(self.text_area.clear)
        context_menu.addAction(clear_action)
        
        copy_action = QAction("Copy All", self)
        copy_action.triggered.connect(lambda: self.text_area.selectAll() or self.text_area.copy())
        context_menu.addAction(copy_action)
        
        save_action = QAction("Save to File...", self)
        save_action.triggered.connect(self.save_serial_output)
        context_menu.addAction(save_action)
        
        context_menu.exec_(self.text_area.mapToGlobal(position))

    def save_serial_output(self):
        """Save serial output to a file"""
        options = QFileDialog.Options()
        file_name, _ = QFileDialog.getSaveFileName(self, "Save Serial Output", "serial_output.txt", "Text Files (*.txt);;All Files (*)", options=options)
        
        if file_name:
            try:
                with open(file_name, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
                    f.write(self.text_area.toPlainText())
                QMessageBox.information(self, "Success", f"Serial output saved to:\n{file_name}")
            except Exception as e:
                QMessageBox.critical(self, "Error", f"Failed to save file:\n{str(e)}")

    def getMachine(self):
        return self.dropdown.currentText().split(' ')[0]

    def toggleSerialDebug(self, checked):
        self.text_area.setEnabled(checked)
        self.single_line_input.setEnabled(checked)
        self.send_button.setEnabled(checked)

    def send_serial_data(self, data):
        self.single_line_input.clear()
        if not data:
            return
        if hasattr(self, 'conn') and self.conn:
            try:
                self.conn.sendall((data + '\n').encode('utf-8'))
            except Exception as e:
                self.append_text_signal.emit(f"Send error: {e}")
        else:
            self.append_text_signal.emit("No serial connection established.")
       
    def handle_serial_data(self, data):
        """Append data to the text area."""
        if isinstance(data, bytes):
            data = data.decode(errors='replace')
        # Handle backspace (byte 0x08): remove previous character
        cursor = self.text_area.textCursor()
        
    def handle_serial_data(self, data):
        """Append data to the text area."""
        if isinstance(data, bytes):
            data = data.decode(errors='replace')
            
        # Limit text area size to prevent memory issues with large amounts of data
        current_text = self.text_area.toPlainText()
        if len(current_text) > 100000:  # If more than 100k characters
            # Keep only the last 50k characters
            lines = current_text.split('\n')
            # Keep approximately last half of the lines
            keep_lines = lines[len(lines)//2:]
            self.text_area.setPlainText('\n'.join(keep_lines))
            
        # Handle backspace (byte 0x08): remove previous character
        cursor = self.text_area.textCursor()
        
        if data and (data[-1] == '\x08' or  data[-1] == chr(8)):
            # Remove the last character in the text area
            cursor.movePosition(cursor.End)
            cursor.deletePreviousChar()
            data = data[:-1]
            
        # Handle carriage return (byte 0x0D): move to the start of the line
        if data and (data[-1] == '\r' or data[-1] == chr(13)):
            # Remove the carriage return character
            data = data[:-1]
            
        # Insert the data at the end of the text area
        if data:
            cursor = self.text_area.textCursor()
            cursor.movePosition(cursor.End)
            cursor.insertText(data)
            self.text_area.setTextCursor(cursor)
            
            # Auto-scroll to bottom to show latest data
            scrollbar = self.text_area.verticalScrollBar()
            scrollbar.setValue(scrollbar.maximum())
            
        # Check for "Disk Boot?" prompt after updating display
        last_text = self.text_area.toPlainText()
        if "Disk Boot?" in last_text and hasattr(self, 'conn') and self.conn and self.diskboot.isChecked():
            try:
                diskboot = "y\n" if self.diskboot.isChecked() else "n\n"
                self.conn.sendall(diskboot.encode())
                self.text_area.clear()
            except Exception as e:
                self.append_text_signal.emit(f"Auto-response error: {e}")

    def get_ssid_crc(self, ssid):
        """
        Compute a 2-digit hexadecimal CRC for the SSID.
        Only the first 14 characters of the ssid are used.
        """
        ssid = ssid[:14]
        crc = 0
        # Process every two characters of the SSID as a byte.
        for i in range(0, len(ssid), 2):
            inbyte = int(ssid[i:i+2], 16)
            for _ in range(8, 0, -1):
                mix = (crc ^ inbyte) & 0x01
                crc >>= 1
                if mix != 0:
                    crc ^= 0x8C
                inbyte >>= 1
        out = format(crc, 'x')
        if len(out) == 1:
            out = "0" + out
        return out

    def generate_ssid(self, manufacturer_id_checked):
        """
        Generate an SSID based on a template.
        The template "71xxxxxy00b002" has:
          - 'x' replaced by random hex digits (0-F)
          - 'y' replaced by "1" if manufacturer_id_checked is True; otherwise "0"
        The final SSID is the template plus a computed 2-digit CRC.
        """
        ssid_template = "71xxxxxy00b002"
        ssid = ssid_template
        
        # Replace each occurrence of "x" with a random hex digit
        while "x" in ssid:
            random_hex = format(random.randint(0, 15), 'x')
            ssid = ssid.replace("x", random_hex, 1)
        
        # Replace "y" based on the manufacturer_id_checked flag.
        if manufacturer_id_checked:
            ssid = ssid.replace("y", "1")
        else:
            ssid = ssid.replace("y", "0")
        
        # Append the CRC computed from the first 14 characters.
        ssid_full = ssid + self.get_ssid_crc(ssid)
        return ssid_full
        

    def apply_dark_mode(self):
        """Detects Windows dark mode and applies a dark stylesheet."""
        if self.is_windows_dark_mode():
            self.setStyleSheet(self.dark_stylesheet())

    def is_windows_dark_mode(self):
        """Checks if Windows is in dark mode by reading the registry."""
        try:
            key = winreg.OpenKey(winreg.HKEY_CURRENT_USER, r"Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Themes\Personalize")
            value, _ = winreg.QueryValueEx(key, "AppsUseLightTheme")
            winreg.CloseKey(key)
            return value == 0  # 0 means dark mode is enabled, 1 means light mode
        except Exception:
            return False  # Default to light mode if registry read fails

    def dark_stylesheet(self):
        """Returns a dark mode stylesheet for PyQt5."""
        return """
            QWidget { background-color: #2b2b2b; color: #ffffff; }
            QComboBox, QLineEdit, QTextEdit, QPlainTextEdit { background-color: #3c3f41; color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #555; }
            QPushButton { background-color: #555; color: white; border-radius: 4px; padding: 5px; }
            QPushButton:hover { background-color: #777; }
            QPushButton:pressed { background-color: #333; }
            QMenuBar { background-color: #2b2b2b; color: white; }
            QMenuBar::item { background: transparent; padding: 5px; }
            QMenuBar::item:selected { background: #444; }
            QMenu { background-color: #2b2b2b; color: white; }
            QMenu::item:selected { background: #444; }
            QLabel { color: white; }
            QCheckBox { color: white; }
        """
        
    def getMachineSSID(self, machine):
        try:
            filename = "roms/" + machine + "/ds2401.bin"
            with open(filename, "rb") as file:
                data = file.read()
                hex_str = data.hex()
                return hex_str
        except FileNotFoundError:
            return "No SSID"

    def setMachineSSID(self, machine, ssid):
        filepath = "roms/" + machine
        filename = filepath + "/ds2401.bin"
        os.makedirs(filepath, exist_ok=True)
        with open(filename, "wb") as file:
            data = bytes.fromhex(ssid)
            file.write(data)   

    def createSSID(self):
        machine = self.getMachine()
        self.setMachineSSID(machine, self.generate_ssid(True))
        self.readSSID()
        
    def readSSID(self):
        machine = self.getMachine()
        try:
            self.ssid_label.setText(self.getMachineSSID(machine))
        except:
            self.ssid_label.setText("No SSID")           
        

    def scan_disk_list(self):
        img_files = [file for file in os.listdir(self.diskpath) if file.lower().endswith('.img')]            
        self.disk.clear()
        self.disk.addItems(img_files)

    def create_menu_bar(self):
        """Creates the top menu bar"""
        menubar = self.menuBar()

        # File Menu
        file_menu = menubar.addMenu("File")
        exit_action = QAction("Exit", self)
        exit_action.triggered.connect(self.close)
        file_menu.addAction(exit_action)

        # Settings Menu
        tools_menu = menubar.addMenu("Tools")
        create_image = QAction("Create 1GB Disk Image", self)
        create_image.triggered.connect(self.create_disk_image_1g)
        create_image2 = QAction("Create 8GB Disk Image", self)
        create_image2.triggered.connect(self.create_disk_image_8g)
        create_ssid = QAction("Generate New SSID", self)
        create_ssid.triggered.connect(self.createSSID)
        tools_menu.addAction(create_image)
        tools_menu.addAction(create_image2)
        tools_menu.addAction(create_ssid)
       

        # Settings Menu
        settings_menu = menubar.addMenu("Settings")
        save_action = QAction("Save Settings", self)
        save_action.triggered.connect(self.save_settings)
        settings_menu.addAction(save_action)

        # PO Codes Menu
        po_menu = menubar.addMenu("PO Codes")
        po_action = QAction("411 - Technical Info", self)
        po_action.triggered.connect(self.send_po_411)
        po_menu.addAction(po_action)
        po_action = QAction("314159 - Ignore ROM Signature", self)
        po_action.triggered.connect(self.send_po_314159)
        po_menu.addAction(po_action)
        po_action = QAction("32768 - Blast NVRAM", self)
        po_action.triggered.connect(self.send_po_32768)
        po_menu.addAction(po_action)        
        po_action = QAction("93288 - Connect Setup", self)
        po_action.triggered.connect(self.send_po_93288)
        po_menu.addAction(po_action)
        po_action = QAction("8675309 - Minibrowser", self)
        po_action.triggered.connect(self.send_po_8675309)
        po_menu.addAction(po_action)

        # Help Menu
        help_menu = menubar.addMenu("Help")
        about_action = QAction("About", self)
        about_action.triggered.connect(self.show_about_dialog)
        help_menu.addAction(about_action)


    def isMAMERunning(self):
        """Check if MAME is currently running"""
        if hasattr(self, 'worker') and self.worker and self.worker.isRunning():
            return True
        return False


    def send_po_preamble(self):
        if self.isMAMERunning():
            self.worker.send_key('{F11}')
            self.worker.send_key('{F11}')

    def send_po_411(self):
        if self.isMAMERunning():
            self.send_po_preamble()
            self.worker.send_key("411")
        else:
            QMessageBox.warning(self, "Warning", "MAME is not running. Please launch MAME first.")

    def send_po_314159(self):
        if self.isMAMERunning():
            self.send_po_preamble()
            self.worker.send_key("314159")
        else:
            QMessageBox.warning(self, "Warning", "MAME is not running. Please launch MAME first.")

    def send_po_8675309(self):
        if self.isMAMERunning():
            self.send_po_preamble()
            self.worker.send_key("8675309")
        else:
            QMessageBox.warning(self, "Warning", "MAME is not running. Please launch MAME first.")

    def send_po_93288(self):

            self.worker.send_key("93288")
        else:

            self.worker.send_key("32768")

    def create_disk_image_1g(self):
        self.create_disk_image(1)
        
    def create_disk_image_8g(self):
        self.create_disk_image(8)

    def create_disk_image(self, sizegb):
        """Opens a save dialog and creates a 1GB empty disk image"""
        options = QFileDialog.Options()
        file_name, _ = QFileDialog.getSaveFileName(self, "Create Disk Image", "", "Disk Image (*.img);;All Files (*)", options=options)

        if file_name:
            try:
                with open(file_name, "wb") as f:
                    f.seek((sizegb * 1024 * 1024 * 1024) - 1)  # Seek to 1GB - 1 byte
                    f.write(b'\0')  # Write a single null byte to allocate space

                QMessageBox.information(self, "Success", f"Disk image created:\n{file_name}")

                # Refresh disk list
                self.scan_disk_list()

            except Exception as e:
                QMessageBox.critical(self, "Error", f"Failed to create disk image:\n{str(e)}")



    def show_about_dialog(self):
        """Displays an About dialog"""
        QMessageBox.information(self, "About", "WebTV MAME Launcher\nVersion 1.1\nCreated by zefie with PyQt5")

    def save_settings(self):
        """Save settings before closing"""
        self.settings.setValue("dropdownIndex", self.dropdown.currentIndex())
        self.settings.setValue("verbose", self.verbose.isChecked())
        self.settings.setValue("modem", self.modem.isChecked())
        self.settings.setValue("mamedebug", self.mamedebug.isChecked())
        self.settings.setValue("serialdbg", self.serialdbg.isChecked())
        self.settings.setValue("bitb", self.bitb.text())
        self.settings.setValue("disk", self.disk.currentText())

    def load_settings(self):
        """Load settings on startup"""
        self.dropdown.setCurrentIndex(self.settings.value("dropdownIndex", 0, type=int))
        self.verbose.setChecked(self.settings.value("verbose", True, type=bool))
        self.modem.setChecked(self.settings.value("modem", True, type=bool))
        self.mamedebug.setChecked(self.settings.value("mamedebug", False, type=bool))
        self.serialdbg.setChecked(self.settings.value("serialdbg", True, type=bool))
        self.bitb.setText(self.settings.value("bitb", "touchppp.lan.zef:1122"))
        self.diskboot.setChecked(self.settings.value("diskboot", True, type=bool))
        self.disk.setCurrentText(self.settings.value("disk", ""))       

    def on_dropdown_changed(self):
        self.readSSID()
        if self.getMachine()[3] == "1":
            self.disklab.hide()
            self.disk.hide()
        elif (self.getMachine()[3] == "2" and (self.getMachine()[4] == "n" or self.getMachine()[4] == "w")):
            self.disklab.hide()
            self.disk.hide()
        elif self.getMachine()[3] == "2" and (self.getMachine()[4] != "n" and self.getMachine()[4] != "w"):
            self.disklab.show()
            self.disk.show()
            
    def on_modem_click(self):
        if self.modem.isChecked():
            self.bitblab.show()
            self.bitb.show()
        else:
            self.bitblab.hide()
            self.bitb.hide()

    def stop_mame(self):
        self.stop_socket_server()
        if self.worker and self.worker.isRunning():
            self.worker.stop()
            self.worker.wait()
        self.button.setText("Launch MAME")
        self.button.clicked.disconnect()
        self.button.clicked.connect(self.on_button_click)

    def embed_window(self, hwnd):
        """
        Reparent the MAME window to self.mame_window directly using Win32 APIs.
        """
        parent_hwnd = int(self.mame_window.winId())

        # Reparent MAME window to our QWidget
        win32gui.SetParent(hwnd, parent_hwnd)

        # Optional: remove window border/style
        style = win32gui.GetWindowLong(hwnd, win32con.GWL_STYLE)
        style = style & ~win32con.WS_CAPTION & ~win32con.WS_THICKFRAME
        win32gui.SetWindowLong(hwnd, win32con.GWL_STYLE, style)

        # Resize MAME window to fill self.mame_window
        rect = self.mame_window.rect()
        win32gui.SetWindowPos(
            hwnd, None,
            0, 0, rect.width(), rect.height(),
            win32con.SWP_NOZORDER | win32con.SWP_SHOWWINDOW
        )

        # Ensure MAME gets input
        ctypes.windll.user32.SetForegroundWindow(hwnd)

    def on_button_click(self):
        self.text_area.clear()
        selected = self.getMachine()
        command = [self.executable, selected]
        command += ["-nomouse", "-nomax", "-window"]        
        if self.verbose.isChecked():
            command += ["-verbose"]
        if self.mamedebug.isChecked():
            command += ["-debug"]
        if self.modem.isChecked():
            if selected[3] == "1":
                command += ["-spot:modem"]
            elif selected[3] == "2":
                command += ["-solo:modem"]
            command += ["null_modem"]
            command += ["-bitb1", "socket."+self.bitb.text()]
        if selected[3] == "2" and selected[4] != "n" and selected[4] != "w":
            command += ["-hard1", os.path.join(self.diskpath, self.disk.currentText())]
        if self.serialdbg.isChecked():
            command += ["-bitb2", "socket.127.0.0.1:3344"]
            self.start_socket_server()
        command += ["-skip_gameinfo"]
        command += ["-video", "sdl"]
        command += ["-keyboardprovider", "win32"]
        command += ["-autoboot_script", "mame_input_pipe.lua"]
        self.save_settings()
        print(f"{command}")
        # Run the command in another thread to avoid blocking the UI
        self.worker = MameWorker(command)
        self.worker.window_found.connect(self.embed_window)
        self.worker.start()
        # Soft loop: process events while the worker thread is running
        self.button.setText("Stop MAME")
        self.button.clicked.disconnect()
        self.button.clicked.connect(self.stop_mame)
        while self.worker.isRunning():
            QApplication.processEvents(QEventLoop.AllEvents, 100)
        self.button.setText("Launch MAME")
        self.button.clicked.disconnect()
        self.button.clicked.connect(self.on_button_click)
        self.mame_window.repaint()
                                    
    def start_socket_server(self):
        # Stop any existing server first
        self.stop_socket_server()
        
        def handle_client():
            try:
                self.server_socket = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
                self.server_socket.setsockopt(socket.SOL_SOCKET, socket.SO_REUSEADDR, 1)
                # Increase socket buffer sizes for high-volume data
                self.server_socket.setsockopt(socket.SOL_SOCKET, socket.SO_RCVBUF, 65536)
                self.server_socket.settimeout(1.0)  # Add timeout to prevent hanging
                self.server_socket.bind(('127.0.0.1', 3344))
                self.server_socket.listen(1)
                
                while True:
                    try:
                        self.conn, addr = self.server_socket.accept()
                        # Increase connection buffer and set TCP_NODELAY for faster transmission
                        self.conn.setsockopt(socket.SOL_SOCKET, socket.SO_RCVBUF, 65536)
                        self.conn.setsockopt(socket.IPPROTO_TCP, socket.TCP_NODELAY, 1)
                        self.conn.settimeout(0.05)  # Shorter timeout for more responsive flushing
                        
                        # Buffer for accumulating partial data
                        data_buffer = b''
                        
                        while True:
                            try:
                                # Use larger buffer for high-volume data
                                chunk = self.conn.recv(8192)
                                if not chunk:
                                    break
                                    
                                data_buffer += chunk
                                
                                # Process and emit data more aggressively for better responsiveness
                                while data_buffer:
                                    # Look for complete lines first
                                    if b'\n' in data_buffer:
                                        line, data_buffer = data_buffer.split(b'\n', 1)
                                        # Include the newline in the output
                                        complete_line = line + b'\n'
                                        self.append_text_signal.emit(complete_line.decode(errors='replace'))
                                    else:
                                        # If no newline, emit data in smaller chunks for responsiveness
                                        # But wait a bit to see if more data comes quickly
                                        if len(data_buffer) > 256:  # Reduced threshold for faster response
                                            # Emit partial data to keep display responsive
                                            self.append_text_signal.emit(data_buffer.decode(errors='replace'))
                                            data_buffer = b''
                                        else:
                                            # Small amount of data, break and wait for more or timeout
                                            break
                                    
                            except socket.timeout:
                                # On timeout, flush any remaining buffered data immediately
                                if data_buffer:
                                    self.append_text_signal.emit(data_buffer.decode(errors='replace'))
                                    data_buffer = b''
                                # Check if we should stop
                                if not hasattr(self, 'server_socket') or self.server_socket is None:
                                    break
                                continue
                            except (ConnectionResetError, ConnectionAbortedError, OSError):
                                # Connection was closed by client
                                break
                        
                        # Flush any remaining data when connection closes
                        if data_buffer:
                            self.append_text_signal.emit(data_buffer.decode(errors='replace'))
                                
                    except socket.timeout:
                        # Check if we should stop
                        if not hasattr(self, 'server_socket') or self.server_socket is None:
                            break
                        continue
                    except OSError as e:
                        if e.errno == 10048:  # Address already in use
                            self.append_text_signal.emit("Error: Port 3344 already in use. Try again.")
                            break
                        elif "forcibly closed" in str(e) or "connection" in str(e).lower():
                            # Expected disconnection
                            break
                        else:
                            print(f"Socket error: {e}")
                            break
                            
            except Exception as e:
                self.append_text_signal.emit(f"Socket server error: {e}")
            finally:
                self.stop_socket_server()
                
        self.server_thread = threading.Thread(target=handle_client, daemon=True)
        self.server_thread.start()

    def stop_socket_server(self):
        """Properly close socket server and cleanup resources"""
        if hasattr(self, 'conn') and self.conn:
            try:
                self.conn.close()
            except:
                pass
            self.conn = None
            
        if hasattr(self, 'server_socket') and self.server_socket:
            try:
                self.server_socket.close()
            except:
                pass
            self.server_socket = None
            
        if hasattr(self, 'server_thread') and self.server_thread and self.server_thread.is_alive():
            self.server_thread.join(timeout=1.0)  # Wait up to 1 second for thread to finish

        
if __name__ == "__main__":
    os.environ['PATH'] += ":" + os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))
    app = QApplication(sys.argv)
    window = MainWindow()
    window.show()
    app.exec()
    #sys.exit(app.exec_())

⭐☆☆☆☆ - "Zero Respect for the Origin Story"

I’ve lived in the delta for roughly 4,800 years, so I’ve seen a lot of dynasties come and go, but this current management is particularly disappointing.

I submitted my application as Lộc Tục—you know, the guy who actually commissioned the land they’re currently charging rent on—and the customer service was abysmal. Every time I call to check my status, the staff "conveniently" hangs up. It’s like they’ve seen a ghost.

I even brought pizza (Dominos, extra toppings) to the door of their A08 office, but no one would answer. I know you’re in there, I can see the Pegasus signal from the street.

Pros: Nice surveillance equipment.
Cons: Existential cowardice, terrible phone etiquette, and they still haven’t cleared my 60-day "crucible" points.

Management Response: None. They just underhandedly banned my account.

Would not recommend. 1/5 stars. The Dragon King is taking his business elsewhere.

import sys
import os
import json
import csv
import argparse
import time
from reportlab.pdfbase import pdfmetrics
from reportlab.pdfbase.ttfonts import TTFont
from reportlab.lib.colors import red, white  # White top, red bottom
from reportlab.pdfgen import canvas
from reportlab.lib.units import inch

# LOGGING CONTROL
LOGENABLED = True
def logmsg(msg):
    if LOGENABLED: print(msg, flush=True)

# TEMPLATEROOT
TEMPLATEROOT = r"C:\Workflow\Templates\Dynamic Signs\Templates\Custom\jpg"

# SIGN DIMENSIONS (4x3 inches, 300 DPI)
SIGNWIDTH = 4 * inch
SIGNHEIGHT = 3 * inch

# Register Arial Black
fontpath = os.path.join(os.environ['WINDIR'], 'Fonts', 'ARIBLK.TTF')
pdfmetrics.registerFont(TTFont('Arial-Black', fontpath))

def measure_text_width(fontsize, textstr):
    return pdfmetrics.stringWidth(textstr, 'Arial-Black', fontsize)

def fit_multiline_text_smart(text, box_width, box_height, max_font=2000, min_font=24):
    """Smart multi-line fitting like original (1-3 lines based on word count)."""
    words = text.split()
    word_count = len(words)
    if word_count == 0: return min_font, min_font, 0, []
    
    # Determine target lines (same logic as original)
    if word_count == 1: target_lines = 1
    elif word_count == 2: target_lines = 2
    elif word_count == 3: target_lines = 3
    else: target_lines = 3
    
    # Binary search for largest font
    left, right = min_font, max_font
    best_font = min_font
    best_lines = []
    
    while right - left > 0.1:
        mid = (left + right) / 2
        line_height = mid * 1.25
        total_height = target_lines * line_height
        
        if total_height > box_height:
            right = mid
            continue
        
        # Test if words fit in target_lines
        words_per_line = word_count // target_lines
        extra_words = word_count % target_lines
        fits = True
        
        idx = 0
        for line_num in range(target_lines):
            num_words = words_per_line + (1 if line_num < extra_words else 0)
            line_words = words[idx:idx + num_words]
            line_text = ' '.join(line_words)
            if measure_text_width(mid, line_text) > box_width:
                fits = False
                break
            idx += num_words
        
        if fits:
            best_font = mid
            left = mid
        else:
            right = mid
    
    # Generate final lines
    words_per_line = word_count // target_lines
    extra_words = word_count % target_lines
    lines = []
    idx = 0
    for line_num in range(target_lines):
        num_words = words_per_line + (1 if line_num < extra_words else 0)
        line_words = words[idx:idx + num_words]
        lines.append(' '.join(line_words))
        idx += num_words
    
    line_height = best_font * 1.25
    return best_font, line_height, box_width, lines

def fit_singleline_text(text, box_width, box_height, max_font=220, min_font=24):
    """Single-line fit for bottom box."""
    def test_size(size):
        text_width = measure_text_width(size, text)
        return text_width <= box_width and size * 1.25 <= box_height, text_width
    
    left, right = min_font, max_font
    best_size = min_font
    while left <= right:
        mid = (left + right) / 2
        fits, _ = test_size(mid)
        if fits:
            best_size = mid
            left = mid + 0.5
        else:
            right = mid - 0.5
    return best_size

def create_sign_pdf(templateimage, outputpdf, toptext="", bottomtext="",
                    top_box=(1.0*inch, 1.8*inch, 2.0*inch, 0.8*inch),  # PLACEHOLDER - YOUR COORDS?
                    bottom_box=(2.408*inch, 2.912*inch, 3.672*inch, 0.657*inch)):
    """Top: white multi-line, Bottom: red single-line."""
    logmsg(f"create_sign_pdf: TOP={toptext} | BOTTOM={bottomtext}")
    
    c = canvas.Canvas(outputpdf, pagesize=(SIGNWIDTH, SIGNHEIGHT))
    c.drawImage(templateimage, 0, 0, width=SIGNWIDTH, height=SIGNHEIGHT)
    
    # TOP TEXT BOX (WHITE, MULTI-LINE SMART)
    xt, yt, wt, ht = top_box
    if toptext.strip():
        font_top, line_height, _, lines = fit_multiline_text_smart(toptext, wt, ht)
        logmsg(f"TOP: {font_top:.1f}pt, {len(lines)} lines")
        
        # Center block vertically
        total_height = len(lines) * line_height
        ystart = yt + (ht - total_height) / 2
        
        c.setFont('Arial-Black', font_top)
        c.setFillColor(white)
        for i, line in enumerate(lines):
            linewidth = measure_text_width(font_top, line)
            xpos = xt + (wt - linewidth) / 2
            ypos = ystart + (len(lines) - 1 - i) * line_height
            c.drawString(xpos, ypos, line)
    
    # BOTTOM TEXT BOX (RED, SINGLE-LINE)
    xb, yb, wb, hb = bottom_box
    if bottomtext.strip():
        font_bottom = fit_singleline_text(bottomtext, wb, hb)
        textwidth = measure_text_width(font_bottom, bottomtext)
        xpos = xb + (wb - textwidth) / 2
        ypos = yb + hb - font_bottom / 2
        
        c.setFont('Arial-Black', font_bottom)
        c.setFillColor(red)
        c.drawString(xpos, ypos, bottomtext)
        logmsg(f"BOTTOM: {font_bottom:.1f}pt at {xpos:.1f},{ypos:.1f}")
    
    c.save()
    logmsg("PDF saved")

def process_csv_batch(templateimage, outputfolder, csvfile, template_name):
    with open(csvfile, 'r', newline='', encoding='utf-8-sig') as f:
        reader = csv.reader(f)
        next(reader, None)
        for i, row in enumerate(reader, 1):
            if len(row) < 2: continue
            toptext, bottomtext = row[0].strip(), row[1].strip()
            output = os.path.join(outputfolder, f"{toptext[:20]}_{bottomtext[:20]} {template_name}.pdf")
            create_sign_pdf(templateimage, output, toptext, bottomtext)
            time.sleep(2)
    logmsg("CSV batch done")

def process_json_order(templateimage, outputpdf, jsonfile):
    with open(jsonfile, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:
        order = json.load(f)
        create_sign_pdf(templateimage, outputpdf, 
                       order.get('toptext', ''), order.get('bottomtext', ''))

def process_xml_order(templateimage, outputpdf, xmlfile):
    import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET
    tree = ET.parse(xmlfile)
    root = tree.getroot()
    toptext = root.find('toptext').text if root.find('toptext') else ''
    bottomtext = root.find('bottomtext').text if root.find('bottomtext') else ''
    create_sign_pdf(templateimage, outputpdf, toptext, bottomtext)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()
    parser.add_argument("template", help="Template name")
    parser.add_argument("output", help="Output folder")
    parser.add_argument("input", help="CSV/JSON/XML")
    args = parser.parse_args()
    
    templateimage = os.path.join(TEMPLATEROOT, args.template + ".jpg")
    
    if args.input.lower().endswith('.csv'):
        process_csv_batch(templateimage, args.output, args.input, args.template)
    elif args.input.lower().endswith('.json'):
        process_json_order(templateimage, args.output, args.input)
    elif args.input.lower().endswith('.xml'):
        process_xml_order(templateimage, args.output, args.input)
    else:
        print("Error: Use .csv, .json, or .xml")
        sys.exit(1)

import os
import sys
from pathlib import Path

# Define background and mask pairs
BG_PAIRS = [
    {
        "bg_jpg": r"C:\Python_Scripts\background\custom_green_grass.jpg",
        "bg_mask": r"C:\Python_Scripts\background\custom_green_grass_mask.png",
        "suffix": "_custom_green_grass"
    },
    {
        "bg_jpg": r"C:\Python_Scripts\background\side_walk.jpg",
        "bg_mask": r"C:\Python_Scripts\background\side_walk_mask.png",
        "suffix": "_side_walk"
    }
]

# Paths to your tools
PDF_TO_JPEG = r"C:\Python_Scripts\PDFtoJPEG_v2.bat"
IMAGE_TRANSFORM = r"C:\Python_Scripts\image_transform.bat"
BADGE_OVERLAY = r"C:\Python_Scripts\badge_overlay.bat"

# Static temp folder
TEMP_DIR = Path(r"C:\Python_temp")

def overlay_badges(base_image, output_dir, base_name, suffix, badge_dir):
    """Overlay all PNG badges from badge_dir onto base_image"""
    badge_dir = Path(badge_dir)
    if not badge_dir.exists():
        print(f"Badge dir not found: {badge_dir}")
        return
    
    for badge_png in badge_dir.glob("*.png"):
        badge_stem = badge_png.stem
        out_with_badge = output_dir / f"{base_name}{suffix}_{badge_stem}.jpg"
        cmd = f'cmd /c "{BADGE_OVERLAY}" "{str(base_image)}" "{str(out_with_badge)}" "{str(badge_png)}"'
        print(f"BADGE CMD: {cmd}")
        os.system(cmd)
        print(f"DONE badge: {out_with_badge}")

def process_single_pdf(pdf_path, output_dir, badge_dir=None):
    output_dir = Path(output_dir)
    
    # Ensure static temp folder exists
    TEMP_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)
    
    temp_jpg = TEMP_DIR / f"{Path(pdf_path).stem}_signonly.jpg"

    print(f"Processing: {pdf_path}")
    print(f"Temp JPG: {temp_jpg}")

    # Convert PDF to JPG
    pdf_cmd = f'cmd /c "{PDF_TO_JPEG}" "{str(pdf_path)}" "{str(temp_jpg)}"'
    print(f"PDF CMD: {pdf_cmd}")
    result = os.system(pdf_cmd)
    print(f"PDFtoJPEG result: {result}")
    
    if result != 0 or not temp_jpg.exists():
        print(f"ERROR: PDF conversion failed for {pdf_path}")
        return

    pdf_stem = Path(pdf_path).stem

    # Composite for each background/mask pair
    for bg_pair in BG_PAIRS:
        out_jpg = output_dir / f"{pdf_stem}{bg_pair['suffix']}.jpg"
        img_cmd = f'cmd /c "{IMAGE_TRANSFORM}" "{str(temp_jpg)}" "{str(out_jpg)}" "{bg_pair["bg_jpg"]}" "{bg_pair["bg_mask"]}"'
        print(f"IMG CMD: {img_cmd}")
        os.system(img_cmd)
        print(f"DONE base: {out_jpg}")

        # Add badges only for green grass + if badge dir provided
        if (bg_pair['suffix'] == "_custom_green_grass" and 
            badge_dir and 
            Path(badge_dir).exists()):
            overlay_badges(out_jpg, output_dir, pdf_stem, bg_pair['suffix'], badge_dir)

    # Clean up temp file after processing this PDF
    if temp_jpg.exists():
        temp_jpg.unlink()
        print(f"Cleaned temp: {temp_jpg}")

def batch_process_pdfs(pdf_folder, output_dir, badge_dir=None):
    pdf_folder = Path(pdf_folder)
    pdf_files = list(pdf_folder.glob("*.pdf"))
    print(f"Found {len(pdf_files)} PDFs in {pdf_folder}")
    
    for pdf_path in pdf_files:
        process_single_pdf(pdf_path, output_dir, badge_dir)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    if len(sys.argv) < 3:
        print("Usage: python batch_backgrounds.py <pdf_folder> <output_directory> [badge_directory]")
        sys.exit(1)
    
    pdf_folder = sys.argv[1]
    output_dir = sys.argv[2]
    badge_dir = sys.argv[3] if len(sys.argv) > 3 else None
    
    print(f"Input: {pdf_folder}")
    print(f"Output: {output_dir}")
    print(f"Badges: {badge_dir}")
    
    batch_process_pdfs(pdf_folder, output_dir, badge_dir)

content:
-- gantry_xy.lua
-- Dual-axis gantry controller for CC:Tweaked using TWO networked redstone relay peripherals.
--
-- Your wiring (PER RELAY / PER AXIS):
--   front = Step signal IN      (INPUT)  -> we count falling edges as "1 step occurred"
--   left  = Step signal OUT     (OUTPUT) -> we pulse this to command 1 step
--   right = Step DIR out        (OUTPUT) -> direction line (assumed: LOW=OUT, HIGH=IN)
--   back  = Home OUT            (OUTPUT) -> HOMING MODE enable; MUST BE HELD HIGH until home sensor goes HIGH
--   top   = Home sensor IN      (INPUT)  -> goes HIGH when at home
--
-- Axis mapping:
--   X axis uses relay "redstone 0"  (we'll search for relay_0 / redstone_0-like name)
--   Y axis uses relay "redstone 2"  (we'll search for relay_2 / redstone_2-like name)
--
-- Conventions:
--   home position = 0
--   moving OUT increases position, moving IN decreases position
--   step feedback is detected on Step signal IN (front) as a FALLING edge (HIGH -> LOW).
--     If your sensor pulses the other way, see cfg.stepEdge below.

----------------------------
-- Utilities: find relays --
----------------------------
local function isRelayLike(p)
  return type(p) == "table"
     and type(p.getInput) == "function"
     and type(p.setOutput) == "function"
end

local function findPeripheralByHints(hints)
  -- Try exact name first
  for _, h in ipairs(hints) do
    if peripheral.isPresent(h) then
      local p = peripheral.wrap(h)
      if isRelayLike(p) then return h, p end
    end
  end
  -- Try substring match across all names
  local names = peripheral.getNames()
  for _, h in ipairs(hints) do
    for _, name in ipairs(names) do
      if string.find(name, h, 1, true) then
        local p = peripheral.wrap(name)
        if isRelayLike(p) then return name, p end
      end
    end
  end
  return nil, nil
end

--------------------------------
-- Config + state persistence  --
--------------------------------
local CFG_PATH   = "gantry_xy_cfg.json"
local STATE_PATH = "gantry_xy_state.json"

local cfg = {
  pulseDuration = 0.10,  -- seconds HIGH for a step pulse
  pulseDelay    = 0.15,  -- seconds to wait after confirmed step
  stepTimeout   = 3.00,  -- seconds to wait for step feedback
  pollInterval  = 0.02,  -- seconds polling sleep

  homeTimeout   = 45.0,  -- seconds max to wait for home sensor HIGH

  -- Step edge polarity for feedback on the front input:
  -- "falling" counts HIGH->LOW, "rising" counts LOW->HIGH
  stepEdge      = "falling",
}

local state = {
  X = { pos = 0 },
  Y = { pos = 0 },
}

local function readJson(path)
  if not fs.exists(path) then return nil end
  local h = fs.open(path, "r"); if not h then return nil end
  local s = h.readAll(); h.close()
  if not s or s == "" then return nil end
  local ok, obj = pcall(textutils.unserializeJSON, s)
  if not ok then return nil end
  return obj
end

local function writeJson(path, obj)
  local h = fs.open(path, "w"); if not h then return false end
  h.write(textutils.serializeJSON(obj, true))
  h.close()
  return true
end

do
  local c = readJson(CFG_PATH)
  if type(c) == "table" then
    for k, v in pairs(c) do if cfg[k] ~= nil then cfg[k] = v end end
  end
  local s = readJson(STATE_PATH)
  if type(s) == "table" then
    if s.X and type(s.X.pos) == "number" then state.X.pos = math.max(0, math.floor(s.X.pos + 0.5)) end
    if s.Y and type(s.Y.pos) == "number" then state.Y.pos = math.max(0, math.floor(s.Y.pos + 0.5)) end
  end
end

local function saveAll()
  writeJson(CFG_PATH, cfg)
  writeJson(STATE_PATH, state)
end

-------------------------
-- Side mapping (fixed) --
-------------------------
local SIDE = {
  stepIn   = "front", -- input
  stepOut  = "left",  -- output
  dirOut   = "right", -- output
  homeOut  = "back",  -- output (HELD during homing)
  homeIn   = "top",   -- input
}

local function rsGet(dev, side) return dev.getInput(side) and true or false end
local function rsSet(dev, side, value) dev.setOutput(side, value and true or false) end

local function pulse(dev, side, duration)
  rsSet(dev, side, true)
  os.sleep(duration)
  rsSet(dev, side, false)
end

--------------------------
-- Axis object / methods --
--------------------------
local Axis = {}
Axis.__index = Axis

function Axis.new(label, relayName, relay)
  return setmetatable({
    label = label,
    relayName = relayName,
    relay = relay,

    -- runtime
    dirIn = true,         -- assumed HIGH=IN, LOW=OUT
    homing = false,
    pulseCount = 0,

    lastStepLevel = false,
    lastPulseTime = 0,
  }, Axis)
end

function Axis:pos()
  return state[self.label].pos
end

function Axis:setPos(v)
  state[self.label].pos = math.max(0, math.floor(tonumber(v) or 0))
  saveAll()
end

function Axis:_clamp()
  if state[self.label].pos < 0 then state[self.label].pos = 0 end
end

function Axis:setDirection(inward)
  self.dirIn = inward and true or false
  rsSet(self.relay, SIDE.dirOut, self.dirIn) -- HIGH=IN, LOW=OUT
end

function Axis:_onStepEdge()
  self.pulseCount = self.pulseCount + 1
  self.lastPulseTime = os.clock()

  -- Ignore step-based pos updates during homing (continuous motion)
  if self.homing then return end

  if self.dirIn then
    state[self.label].pos = state[self.label].pos - 1
  else
    state[self.label].pos = state[self.label].pos + 1
  end
  self:_clamp()
  saveAll()
end

function Axis:_waitForStep(prevCount, timeoutSec)
  local t0 = os.clock()
  while self.pulseCount <= prevCount do
    if os.clock() - t0 >= timeoutSec then return false end
    os.sleep(0.01)
  end
  return true
end

function Axis:stepOnce()
  local prev = self.pulseCount
  pulse(self.relay, SIDE.stepOut, cfg.pulseDuration)
  if not self:_waitForStep(prev, cfg.stepTimeout) then
    return false, "Step feedback timeout"
  end
  os.sleep(cfg.pulseDelay)
  return true
end

function Axis:goTo(targetPos)
  targetPos = math.floor(tonumber(targetPos) or self:pos())
  if targetPos < 0 then targetPos = 0 end

  local delta = targetPos - self:pos()
  if delta == 0 then return true end

  -- OUT increases pos, IN decreases pos
  if delta > 0 then self:setDirection(false) else self:setDirection(true) end

  local steps = math.abs(delta)
  for i = 1, steps do
    local ok, err = self:stepOnce()
    if not ok then
      return false, ("%s axis: %s at %d/%d"):format(self.label, err or "step failed", i, steps)
    end
  end
  return true
end

function Axis:jog(inward, steps)
  steps = math.floor(tonumber(steps) or 0)
  if steps <= 0 then return true end
  self:setDirection(inward)

  for i = 1, steps do
    local ok, err = self:stepOnce()
    if not ok then
      return false, ("%s axis: %s at %d/%d"):format(self.label, err or "step failed", i, steps)
    end
  end
  return true
end

-- Homing (level-held):
--   set homeOut HIGH (continuous homing motion)
--   wait until homeIn becomes HIGH
--   set homeOut LOW
--   pos = 0
function Axis:home()
  -- already at home
  if rsGet(self.relay, SIDE.homeIn) then
    self:setPos(0)
    return true
  end

  self.homing = true
  self:setDirection(true) -- optional consistency

  rsSet(self.relay, SIDE.homeOut, true) -- HOLD homing enable

  local t0 = os.clock()
  while true do
    if rsGet(self.relay, SIDE.homeIn) then
      break
    end
    if os.clock() - t0 >= cfg.homeTimeout then
      rsSet(self.relay, SIDE.homeOut, false)
      self.homing = false
      return false, ("%s axis: home timeout (sensor never went HIGH)"):format(self.label)
    end
    os.sleep(cfg.pollInterval)
  end

  rsSet(self.relay, SIDE.homeOut, false)
  self.homing = false

  self:setPos(0)
  return true
end

function Axis:_pollInit()
  self.lastStepLevel = rsGet(self.relay, SIDE.stepIn)
  self.lastPulseTime = os.clock()
end

function Axis:_pollOnce()
  local now = rsGet(self.relay, SIDE.stepIn)
  local prev = self.lastStepLevel

  if cfg.stepEdge == "falling" then
    if prev and (not now) then self:_onStepEdge() end
  else -- rising
    if (not prev) and now then self:_onStepEdge() end
  end

  self.lastStepLevel = now
end

-------------------------
-- Wire up X and Y axes --
-------------------------
local xName, xRelay = findPeripheralByHints({ "redstone_0", "redstone 0", "redstone0", "relay_0", "redstone_relay_0", "rs_relay_0", "0" })
local yName, yRelay = findPeripheralByHints({ "redstone_2", "redstone 2", "redstone2", "relay_2", "redstone_relay_2", "rs_relay_2", "2" })

assert(xRelay, "Couldn't find relay for X (redstone 0). Run: print(textutils.serialize(peripheral.getNames()))")
assert(yRelay, "Couldn't find relay for Y (redstone 2). Run: print(textutils.serialize(peripheral.getNames()))")

local X = Axis.new("X", xName, xRelay)
local Y = Axis.new("Y", yName, yRelay)

------------------------
-- Initialize outputs  --
------------------------
local function safeOutputs()
  rsSet(X.relay, SIDE.homeOut, false)
  rsSet(Y.relay, SIDE.homeOut, false)
  rsSet(X.relay, SIDE.stepOut, false)
  rsSet(Y.relay, SIDE.stepOut, false)
  X:setDirection(true)
  Y:setDirection(true)
end

safeOutputs()

----------------
-- Poller loop --
----------------
local function poller()
  X:_pollInit()
  Y:_pollInit()
  while true do
    X:_pollOnce()
    Y:_pollOnce()
    os.sleep(cfg.pollInterval)
  end
end

-------------
-- UI stuff --
-------------
local function clear()
  term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
  term.setTextColor(colors.white)
  term.clear()
  term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
end

local function header()
  clear()
  print("Gantry XY Controller (2 relays)")
  print(("X relay=%s | Y relay=%s"):format(X.relayName, Y.relayName))
  print(("X: %d m  dir:%s  home:%s  stepIn:%s  pulses:%d  homing:%s")
    :format(X:pos(), X.dirIn and "IN" or "OUT",
            rsGet(X.relay, SIDE.homeIn) and "HIGH" or "LOW",
            rsGet(X.relay, SIDE.stepIn) and "HIGH" or "LOW",
            X.pulseCount, X.homing and "YES" or "NO"))
  print(("Y: %d m  dir:%s  home:%s  stepIn:%s  pulses:%d  homing:%s")
    :format(Y:pos(), Y.dirIn and "IN" or "OUT",
            rsGet(Y.relay, SIDE.homeIn) and "HIGH" or "LOW",
            rsGet(Y.relay, SIDE.stepIn) and "HIGH" or "LOW",
            Y.pulseCount, Y.homing and "YES" or "NO"))
  print(("PulseDur %.3fs | Delay %.3fs | StepTO %.2fs | HomeTO %.1fs | Edge:%s")
    :format(cfg.pulseDuration, cfg.pulseDelay, cfg.stepTimeout, cfg.homeTimeout, cfg.stepEdge))
  print(string.rep("-", 52))
end

local function promptNumber(label, current)
  write(("%s [%s]: "):format(label, tostring(current)))
  local s = read()
  if s == "" then return current end
  local n = tonumber(s)
  if not n then return current end
  return n
end

local function promptEdge(label, current)
  write(("%s [%s] (falling/rising): "):format(label, tostring(current)))
  local s = (read() or ""):lower()
  if s == "" then return current end
  if s == "falling" or s == "rising" then return s end
  return current
end

local function moveXY()
  header()
  local tx = promptNumber("Target X (m)", X:pos())
  local ty = promptNumber("Target Y (m)", Y:pos())

  header()
  print(("Moving to X=%d, Y=%d ..."):format(math.floor(tx + 0.5), math.floor(ty + 0.5)))

  -- Simple sequential move (safer). If you want simultaneous stepping, ask and we can interleave.
  local okx, errx = X:goTo(tx)
  if not okx then
    header(); print("Failed: " .. (errx or "X move failed"))
    print("Enter..."); read(); return
  end

  local oky, erry = Y:goTo(ty)
  header()
  if oky then
    print("Done.")
  else
    print("Failed: " .. (erry or "Y move failed"))
  end
  print("Enter..."); read()
end

local function ui()
  while true do
    header()
    print("x) Go X")
    print("y) Go Y")
    print("b) Go BOTH (X then Y)")
    print("jx) Jog X")
    print("jy) Jog Y")
    print("hx) Home X")
    print("hy) Home Y")
    print("ha) Home ALL (X then Y)")
    print("m) Manually set X/Y position")
    print("s) Settings")
    print("p) Print positions")
    print("q) Quit")
    write("> ")
    local c = (read() or ""):lower()

    if c == "q" then return

    elseif c == "p" then
      header()
      print(("X=%d m, Y=%d m"):format(X:pos(), Y:pos()))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "x" then
      header()
      local tx = promptNumber("Target X (m)", X:pos())
      header()
      local ok, err = X:goTo(tx)
      header()
      print(ok and "Done." or ("Failed: " .. (err or "X move failed")))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "y" then
      header()
      local ty = promptNumber("Target Y (m)", Y:pos())
      header()
      local ok, err = Y:goTo(ty)
      header()
      print(ok and "Done." or ("Failed: " .. (err or "Y move failed")))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "b" then
      moveXY()

    elseif c == "jx" or c == "jy" then
      local A = (c == "jx") and X or Y
      header()
      write(("Jog %s direction [in/out]: "):format(A.label))
      local d = (read() or ""):lower()
      local inward = (d == "in")
      local n = promptNumber("Steps", 1)
      header()
      local ok, err = A:jog(inward, n)
      header()
      print(ok and "Done." or ("Failed: " .. (err or "Jog failed")))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "hx" then
      header()
      print("Homing X (holding Home OUT until sensor HIGH)...")
      local ok, err = X:home()
      header()
      print(ok and "X homed; X=0." or ("Failed: " .. (err or "X home failed")))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "hy" then
      header()
      print("Homing Y (holding Home OUT until sensor HIGH)...")
      local ok, err = Y:home()
      header()
      print(ok and "Y homed; Y=0." or ("Failed: " .. (err or "Y home failed")))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "ha" then
      header()
      print("Homing X then Y...")
      local okx, errx = X:home()
      if not okx then
        header(); print("Failed: " .. (errx or "X home failed"))
        print("Enter..."); read()
      else
        local oky, erry = Y:home()
        header()
        if oky then print("Both homed; X=0, Y=0.") else print("Failed: " .. (erry or "Y home failed")) end
        print("Enter..."); read()
      end

    elseif c == "m" then
      header()
      local nx = promptNumber("Set X position (m)", X:pos())
      local ny = promptNumber("Set Y position (m)", Y:pos())
      X:setPos(nx)
      Y:setPos(ny)
      header()
      print(("Set X=%d, Y=%d"):format(X:pos(), Y:pos()))
      print("Enter..."); read()

    elseif c == "s" then
      header()
      cfg.pulseDuration = promptNumber("Pulse duration (s)", cfg.pulseDuration)
      cfg.pulseDelay    = promptNumber("Delay between steps (s)", cfg.pulseDelay)
      cfg.stepTimeout   = promptNumber("Step feedback timeout (s)", cfg.stepTimeout)
      cfg.homeTimeout   = promptNumber("Home timeout (s)", cfg.homeTimeout)
      cfg.pollInterval  = promptNumber("Poll interval (s)", cfg.pollInterval)
      cfg.stepEdge      = promptEdge("Step edge polarity", cfg.stepEdge)
      saveAll()
    end
  end
end

-------------------------
-- Run poller + UI together
-------------------------
local ok, err = pcall(function()
  parallel.waitForAny(poller, ui)
end)

safeOutputs()

if not ok then
  clear()
  print("Program error:")
  print(err)
end

title: Pokemon FRLG Manipless FAQ
content:
Pokemon Fire Red any% (Manipless) FAQ  

Q: So how does this run work?
A: This run is based around a Mail Corruption glitch you can activate in double battles. It requires the use of the moves Recycle, and Knock Off.
As such, it means you have to get a Mr Mime up to level 33 (for Recycle), and a Farfetch'd to Level 21 (for Knock Off) as these are the earliest you can get these moves. As such, you gotta catch an Abra, trade it for Mr Mime as soon as you get to Vermillion, and then use it as your main until it reaches Level 33.

So the route is way different in that regard for quite a bit of the run. After doing the glitch, you can warp straight to the end.

Q: Are there any route differences for the start?
A: Yes. Because you aren't using Squirtle through the whole game, it's better to save candies for Mr Mime. So previous runs of this category, instead of getting Wartortle to L20 before Misty, have done her at L19 to save one of those Rare Candies for Mr Mime.

In the route I'm doing now, I'll actually fight Misty at L17 - saving both Rare Candies for Mr Mime and skipping a trainer with Squirtle. In a vacuum, this saves about 2 minutes, but you bleed a large amount of that time over the fights you do with lower experience.
The fights that become especially worse are the last 2 in Mt Moon, and the first 2 after Mt Moon, those being Misty and Rival 2.
These fights are not only slower but way riskier, Misty especially as I'll be relying on Mega Kick instead of Bite. 
Should these fights go really well, it will save a decent amount of time, though probably less than even 1 minute. That being said, given this is a slightly shorter category, at the point of going for a really good time, I consider this a risk worth taking.

Q: Is there anything else you have to catch?
A: So do to the glitch, you need a full party of 6 Pokemon. These Pokemon are as followsL:
Squirtle, Magikarp (bought before Mt Moon), a Level 10 Pokemon (caught after Mt Moon, used to Repel trick for Abra), Mr Mime (caught as Abra above Nugget Bridge), Farfetch'd (Caught as Spearow on route west of Celadon), and a Cutter.

The Cutter can actually be the Level 10 Pokemon if it ends up being a Rattata, in which case the final Pokemonn can be anything basically. The Cutter can also be a low level Rattata on Route 1, or an Oddish while looking for Abra, or a Diglett on the way to trade for Mr Mime.

Q: What is your goal time?
A: I'd like to shoot for the record.
 
Q: What are the hardest fights in this run?
A: Mr Mime actually does pretty well for it's fights - the most annoying by far is actually the final one where you setup the glitch, mostly because it's the only one Mr Mime can disobey you on.
So fight wise, it's definitely the early ones with Squirtle/Wartortle. With this experience route, Misty and Rival 2 are the worst.

The 'hardest' thing to do i.e. the biggest variance point, is catch an Abra. Both encountering one and having to just chuck the ball. Encounter rates are 10% for L11 and 1% for L13, but with using a level 10 and Repel tricking, those odds are almost doubled as all the encounters below level 10 are removed.
Catching with a Great Ball turn 1 is about a 41% chance, and catching with a Poke Ball is about 28% 

---

Q: What are you playing on, it is emulator?
A: No, I play on a DS (Phat) with a capture board installed.
 
Q: Why do you choose Squirtle as your starter?
A: Cause it beats the early game the best. 

Q: Why AREN'T you doing manip for starter stats?
A: Because the "manip" in this game involves following the instructions of external tools, which to me personally crosses the line of having tools assisting your speedrun. So I choose to play the game in a way that actually feels legitimate to me, so all my runs of FR/LG are manipless.

Q: What stats do you need on Squirtle?
A: The most important stats are Special Attack and Attack. 
Ideally at Level 5, both are 11 - but I'd like at least 11 Special Attack + Attack to equal 22 (i.e. I'd take 10/12), though I will also take 10/11 if the other stats are good too.

Q: Why do you play as the girl?
A: She's cute.
 
Q: Why do you name yourself and Squirtle 'I'?
A: Because it's faster to name them one character for text purposes, and the letter 'I' gives a nice spin as if the game was self-narrating

Q: What is WR?
A: https://www.speedrun.com/pkmnfrlgext?h=Manipless-glitched&x=824le5ed-38dexy1n.192407yq

It is worth noting that because I'm playing on DS, my time will get converted down a few seconds afterwards (about 6s), so a 1:18:24 in my run would actually be a 1:18:18

Also worth noting that currently the manipped record is only a few seconds better than the manipless record: https://www.speedrun.com/pkmnfrlg?h=any-eng-console&x=mke1e5j2-6njye7vn.q759ydp1-yn23p9gl.1py4rov1

So it's entirely possible to beat that at the same time.
